    Root cause                                                                  
                                                                                
    The root cause is that david5.data is explicitly initialized to nullptr,    
    but later the program follows a pointer chain that reaches david5.data and  
    dereferences it without checking for null.                                  
                                                                                
    The defective initialization is here:                                       
                                                                                
                                                                                
     David david5 = {nullptr};                                                  
                                                                                
                                                                                
    That object is then reachable through:                                      
                                                                                
                                                                                
     adam1.b2       // &bob2                                                    
          ->c2      // &charlie4                                                
          ->d1      // &david5                                                  
          ->data    // nullptr                                                  
                                                                                
                                                                                
    So this line is unsafe:                                                     
                                                                                
                                                                                
     int n = *adam1.b2->c2->d1->data;                                           
                                                                                
                                                                                
    because it assumes every pointer in the chain is valid, including data.     
                                                                                
    Recommendation                                                              
                                                                                
    Minimal local fix: initialize david5 with a valid int * before it is        
    dereferenced.                                                               
                                                                                
    For example:                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
     David david5 = {&arrayofints[0]};                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    or, if the intended value was the same as david4:                           
                                                                                
                                                                                
     David david5 = {&arrayofints[7]};                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Then this line becomes safe:                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
     int n = *adam1.b2->c2->d1->data;                                           
                                                                                
                                                                                
    A more defensive local fix is to check the pointer chain before             
    dereferencing:                                                              
                                                                                
                                                                                
     if (adam1.b2 &&                                                            
         adam1.b2->c2 &&                                                        
         adam1.b2->c2->d1 &&                                                    
         adam1.b2->c2->d1->data) {                                              
       int n = *adam1.b2->c2->d1->data;                                         
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    A more thorough root-cause fix is to avoid nullable raw pointers for        
    required relationships. If David::data must always point to an integer, do  
    not model it as an optional raw pointer. For example:                       
                                                                                
                                                                                
     struct David                                                               
     {                                                                          
       int &data;                                                               
     };                                                                         
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Then construction must provide a valid integer:                             
                                                                                
                                                                                
     David david5 = {arrayofints[0]};                                           
     int n = adam1.b2->c2->d1->data;                                            
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Alternatively, if data is genuinely optional, use an explicit optional      
    representation and handle the empty case before reading it.                 
                                                                                
